    <div style="display:flex; flex-direction:column;">

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#1c1917; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          What drives property values in Inala?
          <span style="color:#c4912a; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Block size, street position and proximity to bus routes connecting to Darra Station are the key value drivers. Homes on quieter residential streets attract the strongest owner-occupier interest. Well-maintained properties on full-sized blocks with rental histories perform well with investors. Affordability relative to Forest Lake and Oxley is a consistent draw for buyers searching the western corridor at an accessible price point.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#1c1917; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          How long does it take to sell a home in Inala?
          <span style="color:#c4912a; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Well-priced Inala homes typically sell within 28 to 45 days. The buyer pool spans first home buyers, investors and multicultural families, which gives the suburb broad appeal across market segments. Investor-grade properties with strong rental histories can move quickly when priced correctly, as yield-focused buyers are actively searching this price range in Brisbane's western corridor.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#1c1917; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          What is the lifestyle like in Inala?
          <span style="color:#c4912a; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Inala is a multicultural suburb around 15 kilometres west of the CBD with a busy local shopping precinct, diverse food options and a strong community character. Bus routes connect to Darra Station on the Ipswich rail line, providing access to the CBD without a car. The Ipswich Motorway is accessible via Richlands Road for those who drive. It is a practical, affordable suburb with a long-established residential feel and consistent demand from both owner-occupiers and tenants.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#1c1917; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          Is Inala a good suburb to sell in?
          <span style="color:#c4912a; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Inala attracts a steady investor and first home buyer market. As Forest Lake and Oxley have strengthened in price, buyers have progressively moved toward Inala seeking comparable western corridor access at a more attainable entry point. Rental demand is consistently strong, which keeps investor interest active and gives sellers a broad audience spanning multiple buyer profiles. The suburb's affordability and diversity are genuine long-term fundamentals.</p>
      </details>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

